Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
gui_trace_flightline(25.10)                        gui_trace_flightline(25.10)

Name
       gui_trace_flightline  -  Traces  flightlines for the specified instance
       from either the output pins  (with  -sink)  or  the  input  pins  (with
       -source)

Syntax
       gui_trace_flightline

       [-help]

       -inst <instance_name>

       [-max_inout_number <value>]

       {[-sink    -sink_level   <value>   -sink_color   <string>]  |  [-source
       -source_level <value> -source_color <string>]}

       Traces flightlines for the specified instance from  either  the  output
       pins  (with  -sink)  or  the input pins (with -source). The flightlines
       drawn with gui_trace_flightline are not dependent  on  instance  selec-
       tion.    These    flightlines   are   cleared   only   when   you   use
       gui_clear_trace_flightline.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description of the gui_trace_flightline command.

              For a detailed description of the command, use the man  command:
              man gui_trace_flightline.

       -inst <instance_name>
              Specifies  the  name  of  the instance from which the flightline
              starts

       -max_inout_number <value>
              Specifies the maximum number of net terms. If the net  has  more
              terms  than  the specified number, the tool skips this net while
              tracing the flightline.

              Default: 50

       -sink  Traces flightlines from the output pins  of  the  specified  in-
              stance.  You  must also specify -sink_color and -sink_level with
              this option.

              You cannot use this option with any of the -source* options.

       -sink_color <string>
              Specifies the color of the sink trace.

       -sink_level <value>
              Specifies the sink trace level.

       -source
              Traces flightlines from the input  pins  of  the  specified  in-
              stance.  You  must also specify -source_color and  -source_level
              with this option.

              You cannot use this option with any of the -sink* options.

       -source_color <string>
              Specifies the color of the source trace.

       -source_level <value>
              Specifies the source trace level.

Examples
              *

                The   following   command   traces   flightlines    for    the
                DTMF_INST/PLLCLK_INST  instance  from  the  output  pins for 2
                logic levels in the color pink:

                gui_trace_flightline   -inst    DTMF_INST/PLLCLK_INST    -sink
                -sink_level 2 -sink_color pink

              * The    following    command   traces   flightlines   for   the
                DTMF_INST/PLLCLK_INST instance from the input pins for 2 logic
                levels in the color green:

                gui_trace_flightline   -inst   DTMF_INST/PLLCLK_INST   -source
                -source_level 2 -source_color green

